The team Europe won the 2018 Ryder Cup by beating the USA team with a final score of 17.5 to 10.5 at Le Golf National outside Paris, France.
The US has thus lost six consecutive times on European soil and have not won a Ryder Cup in Europe since 1993.
Europe won the trophy once the Danish captain Thomas Bjorn's team reached the 14.5 points needed to beat the United States.
The USA Phil Mickelson champion, who fought for most of the tournament, launched his tee shot into the water at the sixteenth hole of Par 3 giving the victory to Francesco Molinari.
